{"comment": ["Pours light golden colored body with a frothy white head. \r\n\r\nAroma of pale malts and corn. \r\n\r\nTaste is grain, malt, subtle hops. Little skunked.  ", "Pretty standard. Hay, grain, malt and some caramel aroma. Wastery with a bit of hop bitterness to counter sweetness. Boring ", "Tasted many times. Typical Pale lager, with medium carbonation and yeasty/malty/watery finish. Next one please! ", " 440ml can from Campus Central, Reading University. Taste is notably metallic, malts and grains, light carbonation, watery, light body. ", "A: Gold with a big white head. \r\nN: Not much. Some grain\r\nT: Slightly sweet with some bitterness\r\nP: Thin\r\nO: Standard lager.  ", "Drunk it more than one time. Last time keg during a weekend in Paris. Colour is clear yellow with a medium white head. Very common in France. Aroma is malty at most. Taste is poor, some bitterness. Body is medium to light, carbonation is average. Basic beer, more marketing than quality. ", "Pale colouration, average white head, soft carbonation, weak malty aroma, medium sweetness with light bitterness. Hints of malt and grains give a lighter taste. Overall a very easy drinking beer, best served in multitude after a long day ", "Not a bad session beer. A fine drinking lager. Could drink a hundred of these on a hot summer day! ", "Bottled. Poured clear golden/amber with an average sized frothy white head. Aroma is sweet, malty, grain, caramel and straw. Medium to heavy sweetness, light bitterness. Light body, slight oily and watery texture, soft to average carbonation. Finish is malty with touch of citrus. ", "330ml bottle from Systembolaget. Clear golden, medium size and long lasting white head, good lacing. Very faint aroma, sweet grains and bread. Light and fairly crisp feel, medium to high carbonation that works alright with the light body. Nothing too much going on in the taste, sweet white bread, grains and grass. Low bitterness.  "], "beer_name": "Kronenbourg 1664", "user": ["MarcoBasile", "Myonlyvice", "Taboada", "coil", "dimeon", "Tinaccio", "chocolatepoppa", "tntracey", "Grumbo", "Turtles"], "nr_reviews": ["467", "369", "1559", "199", "518", "550", "7", "119", "4392", "3148"], "score": "1.5 out of 5.0<br /><small>Aroma 3/10<br />Appearance 2/5<br />Taste 3/10<br />Palate 2/5<br />Overall 5/20<br /></small"}
