{"comment": ["Bi\u00e8re blonde de 5 % d\u2019alcool. Elle poss\u00e8de un odorat de bi\u00e8re commerciale ( O\u2019Keefe) et de moufette. Elle poss\u00e8de un petit col mousseux au versement. Elle poss\u00e8de un go\u00fbt \u00e2cre, l\u00e9g\u00e8rement amer, mais l\u2019amertume reprend en finale. Elle poss\u00e8de \u00e9galement un petit go\u00fbt sal\u00e9. Correcte et rafra\u00eechissante. ", "Better than expected. Grassy aroma. Light golden color with a light, highly carbonated palate. Flavors where of cereal and lager yeast. Some hop presence. Easy to drink. ", "500ml can. (5% ABV) Pours a clear gold with a medium, creamy, long lasting, white head that leaves curtains of lace. Mild aroma of wheat malt and corn. Sweet flavour of wheat malt, caramel and corn with mild grass bitterness in the finish. Light body with a watery texture and soft carbonation. Smooth and easy drinking.  ", "A small bottle from Jason\u2019s near NCCU, drunk at home. Aroma: a faint suggestion of hops, floral. Appearance: Clear golden, minimal head. Palate: light-bodied, rather thin, average carbonation, some bitterness at the end. Taste: lightly bitter with a faintly sweet aftertaste. Unexceptional, too much of this will probably give you tummy ache. ", "Piwo barwy z\u0142otej, piana \u015brednio obfita, ltrwa\u0142a. W aromacie s\u0142odowa s\u0142odycz. W ss\u0142odowe, lecz do\u015b\u0107 wytrawne i kwaskowate. ", "On tap for this review, but I\u2019ve had plenty of times from bottle, can and tap before. Pours pale straw with decent head. Aroma is generic lager: vinegar and vegetable stuff. Flavour has a little fruitiness to it as well. One of those beers where I\u2019ve drunk a lot during my life, but when forced to actually think about what it tastes like, I\u2019ve no idea why. ", "Cerveza de estilo pale lager media. Aroma suave y escaso, apariencia amarillo p\u00e1lido, sabor agradable pero muy suave (cuerpo bajo) y paladar correcto pero casi imperceptible. ", " Color Biondo, poca schiuma, al naso tanti cereali, anche al palato dolcezza di malto e cereali. Carbonazione medio alta.  ", "Francuski przedstawiciel stylu. Lager jakich wiele. S\u0142abo wyczuwalny chmiel. ", "Canned. It\u2019s hard to distinguish these mass-produced lagers but I\u2019ve had many worse. "], "beer_name": "Kronenbourg 1664", "user": ["Tricker", "kevinator", "cmacklin", "Luneylane", "ROSE1962", "explosivedog", "MAGICuenca91", "lello4ever", "caketm", "midovark"], "nr_reviews": ["423", "2880", "1405", "277", "333", "1885", "82", "1274", "436", "1161"], "score": "3 out of 5.0<br /><small>Aroma 5/10<br />Appearance 3/5<br />Taste 6/10<br />Palate 3/5<br />Overall 13/20<br /></small"}
